<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{6}{y}=-{40}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}-{3}{y}={42}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2},-{8}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{6}{y}=-{40}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}=-{40}-{\left({6}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{40}-{\left({6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{\left(\frac{{-{40}-{\left({6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}\right)}+-{3}{y}={42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{9}}{{-{{4}}}}\cdot{\left(-{40}\right)}--\frac{{9}}{{-{{4}}}}{\left({6}\right)}{y}+-{3}{y}={42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{90}-{\left(-{13.5}\right)}{y}+-{3}{y}={42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{13.5}{y}+{\left(-{3}\right)}{y}={42}--{90}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{13.5}{y}+{\left(-{3}\right)}{y}={132}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{13.5}+{\left(-{3}\right)}\right)}{y}={132}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{16.5}{y}={132}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{132}}{{-{{16.5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{6}{\left(-{8}\right)}=-{40}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{\left(-{48}\right)}=-{40}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}=-{40}-{\left(-{48}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{8}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2},-{8}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

